The paper discusses connections between matrix rigidity, communication complexity, and circuit lower bounds, which are all topics typically studied in theoretical computer science. Specifically, the paper introduces a new notion of probabilistic rank and sign-rank for matrices, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
